Custom functions

# function for getting lnRR for proportional data

lnrrp <- function(m1, m2, n1, n2) {
  # arcsine transforamtion
  asin_trans <- function(p) { asin(sqrt(p)) }
  # SD for arcsine distribution (see Wiki - https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arcsine_distribution)
  var1 <- 1/8
  var2 <- 1/8
  # lnRR - with 2nd order correction
  lnrr <- log(asin_trans(m1)/asin_trans(m2)) + 
    0.5 * ((var1 / (n1 * asin_trans(m1)^2)) - (var2 / (n2 * asin_trans(m2)^2))) 
  
  var <- var1 / (n1 * asin_trans(m1)^2) + var1^2 / (2 * n1^2 * asin_trans(m1)^4)  + 
    var2 / (n2 * asin_trans(m2)^2) + var2^2 / (2 * n2^2 * asin_trans(m2)^4) 
  
  invisible(data.frame(yi = lnrr , vi = var))
}

# function for getting lnRR for mean data

lnrrm <- function(m1, m2, n1, n2, sd1, sd2) {
  # lnRR - with 2nd order correction
  lnrr <- log(m1/m2) + 
    0.5 * (((sd1^2) / (n1 * m1^2)) - ((sd2^2) / (n2 * m2^2)))   
  
  var <- sd1^2 / (n1 * m1^2) + sd1^4 / (2 * n1^2 * m2^4)  + 
    sd2^2 / (n2 * m2^2) + sd2^4 / (2 * n2^2 * m2^4) 
  
  invisible(data.frame(yi = lnrr , vi = var))
}

#extract publication year from Study variable

Summarise the dataset

Note that ES have not been calculated yet (use prelim.R code to do so).

Look at the overall pattern of missing data.

General summary

  • Number of effect sizes: 116
  • Number of studies: 50
  • Publication years: from 1930 to 2021
  • Simmple list of studies as short references: Kirkpatrick and Turner 2004, Jacob et al 2004 A, Jacob et al 2004 B, Twigg et al 2000, Gibbs and Jewel 1996, Zakeri et al 2019, Dorner and Tabelle 1973, Asdell et al 1967, Asdell and Goshi 1975, Arriola Apelo et al 2020, Benedusi et al 2015, Cargil et al 2003, Cox et al 2014, Cox and Calsbeek 2010, Cox et al 2010, Reedy et al 2016, Drori and Folman 1976, Garratt et al 2021, Hamilton et al 1969, Waters et al 2011, Holland et al 1997, Kirkman and Yau, Sichuk 1965, Mitchel et al 1999, Moore et al 2001, Nieschlag et al 1993, Slonaker 1930, Storer et al 1982, Hoffman et al 2018, Mason et al 2009, Talbert and Hamilton 1965, Tapprest et al 2017, Hamilton 1965, Huang et al 2017, Min et al 2012, Williams et al 2007, Urfer et al 2019, Ramsey 2000, Ramsey et al 2021, Muhlock 1959, Jewel 1997, Iwasa et al 2018, Hamilton and Mestler 1969, Oneil et al 2013, Oneil et al 2015, Parker et al 2013, Wilson et al 2019, Cheng 2019, Bronson 1981, Bronson 1982
  • Number of species: 14
  • Simple list of species Latin names (also stored in “Phylogeny” variable): Equus ferus, Rattus argentiventer, Oryctolagus cuniculus, Myodes glareolus, Mus musculus, Rattus norvegicus, Anolis sagrei, Felis catus, Canis lupus, Mesocricetus auratus, Homo sapiens, Trichosurus vulpecula, Phascolarctos cinereus, Ovis aries
  • Number of data points for females: 68, and data points form males: 48
